George Fisher (actor) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/George_Fisher_(actor) 0 George Fisher (August 10, 1891 – August 13, 1960) was an American film actor of the silent era. He appeared in 72 films between 1911 and 1929. His role in the 1916 Thomas H. Ince film Civilization is noteworthy as the first cinematic depiction of Jesus.
